RACE.FOOTNOTES: STEALING APRIORITY pressed two wide and between a pair of rivals while under steady urging into the turn, vied around the bend, kicked clear leaving the quarter pole, and held sway under a drive. ARCTIC ROSE pressed outside of the top pair and from the four path around the turn, failed to keep pace with an inner counterpart while spinning into the lane in the five path, then chased that foe home well to prove second best. HEREWECOMETOGETYOU laid off of the pace in the two path, inched closer turning for home before fanning to the six, then seven, path in upper stretch, claimed show in approaching midstretch while staying on willingly as he hung on his left lead, and failed to menace after changing leads in the final sixteenth. ARGYBARGY BUCK trailed in the three path, swung to the seven path entering the lane, and moved up. GENERAL EISENHOWER laid off of the pace along the inside, and never got involved while hanging on his left lead. INTHEALY quickly sped to the front and crossed over, was confronted by a pair of outer pressers at the half mile pole, got headed by them approaching the five sixteenths marker, and weakened through the lane while requiring correction from attempting to lug out.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SIKUM tracked two wide and between horses, got keen while running into the leader's kickback while among foes at the nine sixteenths pole, settled into stride into the turn, pursued from behind the leaders around the bend, dove inwardly to a rail seam leaving the quarter pole, slipped through to bid inside of the leading trio at the three sixteenths pole, forged an advantage at the furlong grounds, and kicked clear. MADAM HENNY tracked outside of the leading pair and from the four path around the turn, produced a bid in upper stretch, but was outkicked by an inner bidder approaching the final sixteenth. NOSTALGIA took a brush from an outer rival at the start, set the pace inside of pressing foes while in the two path, dug in turning for home, vied between horses in upper stretch as the eventual winner produced a rail bid, but was headed at the furlong grounds, and yielded in the late stages. THINKITASADONATION prompted the leader from the three path, bid turning for home, vied between horses in upper stretch as rivals bid on either side, then yielded at the furlong grounds. TEXAS TIDELANDS leaned in at the start and was off a bit slow, lagged behind along the inside around the bend, cut the gap entering the lane, and improved two wide and between horses in midstretch while hanging on her left lead. PI YO PRINCESS lacked speed in the four path, then shied to the seven path leaving the quarter pole when an inner rival bore across her path, and made little impact. BLUEBIRD SING broke a step slowly, laid off of the pace along the inside, bore out to the nine path passing the quarter pole, and tired on her left lead. MEDWAY QUEEN leaned in and brushed a rival at the start, stalked along the inside, but weakened turning for home.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: UNIFIED DREAMS vied along the inside around the first turn before allowing an outer rival to set the pace nearing the backstretch, rated back to stalk from the inside, tipped outside of the top pair turning for home as their only challenger, sustained a bid at the three sixteenths pole, dueled with an inner game rival while hanging on his left lead through the final furlong, and prevailed. TRIGGER HAPPY emerged from between horses to set the pace two wide into the first turn, cleared and tucked to the inside entering the backstretch, resisted an outer bid turning for home, repelled that foe as an outer UNIFIED DREAMS menaced approaching midstretch, dueled gamely with that foe through the final furlong while hanging on his left lead, but was bested. GIANNIS lacked speed four wide, but was through after a half mile, and eased through the lane. PRINCE OF GLORY laid off of the pace three wide and between horses, failed to respond to urging into the far turn, weakened before being eased around that bend, then strolled to the wire before walking off.
